word_group.brief_definition: 最高法院；英国最高法院；美国联邦最高法院
最高权力；至高无上的权力

bilingual.source: The chef prepared a dish of supreme quality.
bilingual.target: 厨师准备了一道最高的品质的菜肴。

bilingual.source: The supreme court is the highest judicial authority in the country.
bilingual.target: 最高的法院是该国的最高司法权威。

bilingual.source: 53，The safety of the people is the supreme law。
bilingual.target: 人民的安全是最高的法律。
最大的决心会产生最高的智慧。

bilingual.source: The supreme governmental power is to be thought.
bilingual.target: 最高的统治力量注定会是思想。

bilingual.source: He is the Supreme Soul and the supreme shelter of all beings.
bilingual.target: 祂是至高无上的灵魂，所有生物最高的庇护所。

bilingual.source: It is often added that there is a supreme Essence (Being): by which is meant God.
bilingual.target: 又有人说，有一个最高的本质，因而称上帝是最高的本质。

bilingual.source: Ii Here the Tathagata became fully enlightened in unsurpassed, supreme Enlightenment!
bilingual.target: 这里如来获得了完全的觉悟，最高的觉悟！

bilingual.source: Currently, the only counterforce to the power of the capital is the supreme political power.
bilingual.target: 目前在中国能够对抗资本强大力量的只有最高的政治权利.

bilingual.source: Emerson said: "The responsibility of the supreme value, it is a great character, in all the value it is in the highest position."
bilingual.target: 爱默生说：“责任具有至高无上的价值，它是一种伟大的品格，在所有价值中它处于最高的位置。”

list.abstract: Supreme是英国人Jame Jebbia在纽约创立的时尚滑板品牌，创立地点在美国纽约，创立时间为1994年。 Supreme主营时尚文化服装，产品有帽子、衬衣、滑板等。 Supreme总收入将在2022财年达到6亿美元，但在2023财年其收入却从5.61亿美元下跌至5.23亿美元，净利润从8240万美元下跌至6480万美元。
supreme[suː'priːm]，英文单词，意为最高的、至高的。

yingyinNormal.en: Kung Fu. It means, "Supreme skill from hard work."
yingyinNormal.zh: 功夫，它的意思是"苦练所得的高超技艺"。

yingyinNormal.en: A Supreme Court confirmation in the middle of an election?
yingyinNormal.zh: 大选期间确认最高法院提名？

yingyinNormal.en: Grand Supreme Little Darling, New York Division? That's me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 超级小可爱，纽约区。那便是我！

yingyinNormal.en: The Supreme Leader believes it is a hallmark of prosperity and self-sufficiency.
yingyinNormal.zh: 高高在上的金将军相信这是北韩标志性的繁荣和自给自足的能力。

yingyinNormal.en: I guess now I can add "Fish poop remover" to my resume next to "Supreme court intern."
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想我现在可以在我简历上的"最高法院实习生"后加上"鱼粪清洁员"。

yingyinNormal.en: Why do you care? You're gonna be a Supreme Court justice. Why does this even matter to you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为何还这么在意，你就要成为最高法院法官了，这一切跟你还有什么关系？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Inspector Gadget. And I want to say Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg. So close. Kooth Bader Ginsburg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 神探加杰特。你的话我猜我国现任最高法院法官鲁斯·巴德·金斯伯格。很接近了。是库萨斯·巴德·金斯伯格。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't understand, Heather. I offered you a seat on the Supreme Court. If Jacobs was stepping down, which he isn't.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不理解，希瑟，我给了你最高法院的位置。前提是雅各布斯辞职，但他不会。

yingyinNormal.en: It's very nice talking to you, Alicia. You could make it all the way to the Supreme Court, Alicia. You're that amazing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很高兴跟你聊天，艾丽西娅，你可以一路走到最高法院，艾丽西娅，你有那么棒。

yingyinNormal.en: The Congress is in disarray, the Supreme Court is down a justice and doomed to deadlock, and the executive branch is without a boss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 国会吵成一团，最高法院少了一位法官，必将陷入僵局，而行政机关也群龙无首。

yingyinNormal.en: Not according to the Supreme Court. In Maryland v. King... Which is a general rule. The specific law in this state, Your Honor, is very, very clear about that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但根据马里兰对金案的最高法院判定，这是一般条款，而我说的是这个州的特别法，法官阁下，对这一点规定可是非常明确的。

yingyinNormal.en: No. Also, I'm pulling the Toobin piece on the Supreme Court women, woman. And I need to see a new draft on that piece about shopping for a plastic surgeon. It's dull.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行 还有，图比做的那篇，关于最高法院里的女性，不能上，还有那篇关于选购整形手术医生的文章要重写，太平淡了。

yingyinNormal.en: Supreme Leader Kim, when the United States, which has an enormous stockpile of nuclear weapons, insists that countries like yours have none, does that feel hypocritical to you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 最高领袖，金，当美国拥有巨大的核武库存时，而像你的国家却没有，这是否让你觉得虚伪。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, technically, the Supreme Court wouldn't determine a defendant's guilt or innocence in a criminal matter. They could only reverse or revamp a jury's conviction based on a constitutional or statutory issue.
yingyinNormal.zh: 严格来说，最高法院并不会裁定一名被告在一起刑事案件中是有罪还是无罪。它们只能把一个法官的判决根据宪法或法规上的问题进行驳回或改进。

examination_example.sentence: The case may yet reach the <highlight>Supreme</highlight> Court.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此案可能会提交最高法院。

examination_example.sentence: The ethical judgments of the <highlight>Supreme</highlight> Court justices have become an important issue recently.
